[vc_row el_id="faq_print"][vc_column width="1/4"][ultimate_heading main_heading="FAQ" main_heading_color="#ffffff" alignment="left" el_class="faq_h" main_heading_style="font-weight:700;" main_heading_font_size="desktop:16px;" main_heading_margin="margin-bottom:15px;" main_heading_font_family="font_family:Lato|font_call:Lato|variant:700"][/ultimate_heading][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1534748622129{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"][vc_toggle title="What happens when shipping rates change?" color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:14|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lora%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534736460623{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 10px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;padding-left: 10px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
The Shipping Wizard tool is synced to the actual shipping service's computers to get their rates in real time. Thus, it automatically and instantly updates to reflect any rate or service changes that a shipping carrier has made. It does the legwork for you!

Created by:

Lcukyluke on September 14, 2017

[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="What if I use a specialized freight service to ship my large items?" color="black" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:14|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lora%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534736391438{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 10px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;padding-left: 10px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
There is a shipping option to select for Freight Service when the price cannot be determined ahead of time.

Created by:

Lcukyluke on September 14, 2017

[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Why are my item pages not showing my price for International shipping?" color="black" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:14|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lora%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534736400051{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 10px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;padding-left: 10px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
When you are signed into your own shop and are viewing your item pages, Antique's system automatically knows where you are located, and will display the price for shipping the item to your country.

Created by:

Lcukyluke on September 14, 2017

[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Why is it important to enter accurate shipping information when I list my items?" color="black" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:14|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lora%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534736407844{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 10px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;padding-left: 10px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
Determined After Checkout is no longer a shipping option available to US based shops. For large items which require specialist packing and transport, the Freight option may be selected, and then the shipping can be calculated by the shop owner after the buyer has submitted the Purchase Order.

Created by:

Luckyluke on September 14, 2017

[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How will the Shipping Wizard be able to calculate the shipping without knowing the zone it is going to?" color="black" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:14|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lora%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534736420237{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 10px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;padding-left: 10px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
Buyers must register with a shipping address before they can make a purchase on Antique. The Shipping Wizard then automatically calculates the total from your shop's zip code to the buyer's zip code.

Created by:

Lcukyluke on September 14, 2017

[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_wp_categories][vc_wp_tagcloud taxonomy="product_cat"][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_row_inner el_class="faq_main"][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1534747349841{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"][ultimate_heading main_heading="MOST FAQ" main_heading_color="#fc6058" heading_tag="h4" alignment="left" spacer="icon_only" icon="Defaults-edit pencil-square-o" icon_size="18" icon_color="#fc6058" main_heading_style="font-weight:700;" main_heading_font_size="desktop:18px;" main_heading_font_family="font_family:Lato|font_call:Lato|variant:700"]How to manage your account and it's features.[/ultimate_heading][vc_toggle title="How can the Shipping Wizard compute an accurate shipping cost on multiple-item orders?" color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534746661092{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
The calculator is designed to consider the combination of items before it determines the true shipping cost.  Simply combining the weight and dimension of each item does not allow for an accurate shipping cost.
Created by: Luckyluke on September 14, 2017
[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Do you ship internationally? Do you ship to Canada? Do you ship to the UK? Do you ship to Australia?" color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534746668658{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
We currently ship to Australia, Canada, Germany, France, Hong Kong, Italy, Japan, Korea, Mexico, New Zealand, Russia, Singapore, Switzerland, and the UK. We’re working hard to expand across the globe. Let us know where we should ship next by contacting: support@gmail.com
Created by: Tuan Ha on December 11, 2017
[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Can I change the shipping address for one of my orders? " color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534746674624{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
As long as your order has not been sent to our shipping and packing department at our warehouse, you can change the shipping address for your order in your account. Click on the link next to your order to change your shipping address. If a link to change your shipping address does not appear, your order has either already shipped or has been sent to shipping and packing at our warehouse.
Created by: Tuan Ha on December 11, 2017
[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="What is an undeliverable package?" color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534746681079{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
Occasionally packages are returned back to our warehouse because the shipper has determined the package is undeliverable. When the carrier returns an undeliverable package to us, we automatically restock the items and issue a full refund (including shipping) back to the original form(s) of payment. Please note: If your package was returned to our warehouse as undeliverable, we will not be able to re-ship your package.
Created by: Alisia on December 11, 2017
[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How much does International Shipping cost? " color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534746687089{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
To learn more about shipping costs and delivery for orders outside the U.S. please refer to our international FAQ page.
Created by: Tuan Ha on December 11, 2017
[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class="faq_main"][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1534747359857{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"][ultimate_heading main_heading="SHIPPING" main_heading_color="#fc6058" heading_tag="h4" alignment="left" spacer="icon_only" icon="Defaults-truck" icon_size="18" icon_color="#fc6058" main_heading_style="font-weight:700;" main_heading_font_size="desktop:18px;" main_heading_font_family="font_family:Lato|font_call:Lato|variant:700"]Commonly asked question about shipping[/ultimate_heading][vc_toggle title="How do I use Facebook to promote my shop?" color="mulled_wine" custom_font_container="tag:h2|font_size:18px|text_align:left" custom_google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal" use_custom_heading="true" css=".vc_custom_1534747458808{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 15px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 15px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ebebeb !important;}"]
Antique on Facebook. Social networking is an important part of an online business. We want to let all shops know that Antique is active on Twitter, Google+, Pinterest, Instagram and Facebook, and we invite you to join us. All services are free to join and as a shop owner you can use these services to promote your own shop too.

item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

TIt is our policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect while operating our website.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
  • Personal information Before using certain parts of any Printshop.com or ordering Products, you must complete an online registration form. During registration, you will be prompted to provide to us certain personal information, including but not limited to User’s (your/company) name, shipping and billing address, phone number, email address, and credit card number. In addition, we may also ask you for your/Customer’s country of residence and/or organization’s country of operation, so we can comply with applicable laws and regulations, and for your gender. These kinds of personal information are used for billing purposes, to fulfill orders, to communicate about order and Printshop, and for internal marketing purposes. If we encounter a problem when processing the order, your personal information may be used to contact you. By registering at Printshop.com, you agree that all information provided in the registration data is true and accurate and that you will maintain and update this information as required in order to keep it current, complete, and accurate. Printshop may collect statistics about the behavior of visitors to its Site. Printshop may display this information publicly or provide it to others. However, Printshop does not disclose personal information other than as described here. If you are a registered user of a Printshop Site and have supplied your email address, Printshop may occasionally send you an email to tell you about new features, new Products, solicit your feedback. Printshop takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against count for any reason, in our sole discretion.
  • Disclosure of information We do not sell or rent, your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes without Your explicit consent. We may disclose personal information to respond to legal requirements, enforce our policies, respond to claims that a content violates other’s rights, or protect anyone’s rights, property, or safety. We may also share personal information with: Service providers who help with our business operations and assist in the delivery of Products or Services to our users. These service providers are under confidentiality agreements with us; Law enforcement or other government officials in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, violations of law, or as otherwise required by law
  • Security Your account is protected by a password for your privacy and security. You need to prevent unauthorized access to your account and personal information by selecting and protecting your password appropriately and limiting access to your computer and browser by signing off after you have finished accessing your account.
  • Privacy policy changes Although most changes are likely to be minor, Printshop may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Printshop’s sole discretion. Printshop encourages you to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this Site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.

item.title: Five Best Photo-Printing Sites
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Digital cameras are fantastic for letting us experiment, take tons of photos, and search for the perfect shot. Digital picture frames and at-home prints are often poor substitutes for real photos. Get a great print at one of these five photo-printing sites.
Once upon a time people took photos and dutifully carted their film down to the photo shop to get developed, waiting to see how the photos turned out. Now people immediately check whether or not the shot was good on the display of their digital camera, and more often than not stuff the photos onto their hard drives or upload them to their Flickr accounts, but never get around to actually printing them and preserving them in a physical form. If you’ve been meaning to get around to printing more photos and saving them from their fate of digital obscurity, the following five Lifehacker reader-selected sites can help you.

item.title: Roach Graphic T-shirt Bundle: 119 ready to print graphics for only $43
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
One of my favorite illustrators, Dan who goes by the creative name of Roach Graphics, is having a major sale on all his artwork, in the form of a bundle. There’s a massive collection of 119 high quality t-shirt prints that can build you an impressive t-shirt line, for only $43!
He is one of our oldest collaborators and one of the best selling creatives on the site since we opened this section, so he has been a big supporter of the Tshirt Factory projects. His recent art hints at pop culture figures, but with a rather versatile style, depending on the subject, he also touches upon themes like cars and bikes, urban, sports, propaganda or motivational slogans.
The approach is both serious and humorous at times, with complex details or on the contrary, simple lines that focus on suggesting an idea rather than describing it. The illustrations can also be used for stickers as promo material for your t-shirt line, because many of them look like mascots or personified popular objects, such as a boombox, a stack of cash, a donut, a polaroid camera or a baseball ball.

item.title: Five Best Photo-Printing
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Digital cameras are fantastic for letting us experiment, take tons of photos, and search for the perfect shot. Digital picture frames and at-home prints are often poor substitutes for real photos. Get a great print at one of these five photo-printing sites.
Once upon a time people took photos and dutifully carted their film down to the photo shop to get developed, waiting to see how the photos turned out. Now people immediately check whether or not the shot was good on the display of their digital camera, and more often than not stuff the photos onto their hard drives or upload them to their Flickr accounts, but never get around to actually printing them and preserving them in a physical form. If you’ve been meaning to get around to printing more photos and saving them from their fate of digital obscurity, the following five Lifehacker reader-selected sites can help you.
